        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/kirsty-coventry-new-president-ioc-144th-session-march-2025-cost-navarino.png" alt="Kirsty Coventry reacts as she is elected the new president of the International Olympic Committee (IOC) at the 144th IOC Session, Costa Navarino, Pylos, Greece" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Kirsty Coventry reacts as she is elected the new president of the International Olympic Committee (IOC) at the 144th IOC Session, Costa Navarino, Pylos, Greece. Credits: Reuters
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The next president of the International Olympic Committee (IOC), Kirsty Coventry, has stated that she wouldn’t <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-24-03-2025-h1-1-automatically-ban-countries" target="_blank">automatically ban countries</a> for participating in international conflicts. She expressed the need for a more nuanced approach, implying that each situation should be evaluated. Coventry suggests implementing a task force to develop guiding policies for handling conflicts within the Olympics.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">She also noted that banning countries because of conflicts felt hypocritical since there are other ongoing conflicts where athletes have not been banned. Coventry cited different conflicts from her home continent of Africa, while many critics have raised the issue of Israel getting to compete. The IOC banned Russia from the 2024 Paris Olympics over the war in Ukraine.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Russian athletes could compete as neutral individuals without representing their country’s flag or anthem. It remains uncertain if Russia will be allowed to return to the 2028 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles. Coventry says the newly established task force will discuss the issue further. President Putin has been pushing for the country's reinstatement in international sports.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
