              margin-top: 2px !important;">X sues India 
        </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/elon-musk-meets-indian-prime-minister-narendra-modi-washington-dc.png" alt="Elon Musk meets Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi in Washington, DC, United States" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Elon Musk meets Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi in Washington, DC, United States. Credits: @narendramodi via X/via Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
      
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Elon Musk’s X has filed a new lawsuit against India’s IT Ministry. Musk accuses it of unlawfully <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-24-03-2025-h2-2-expanding-censorship-powers" target="_blank">expanding censorship powers</a> through a new content-blocking mechanism. The platform alleges that the ministry directs various government departments to use a Home Affairs-run website to issue takedown orders that bypass strict legal safeguards under India’s IT Act.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">India’s IT Act allows censorship only in cases threatening sovereignty or public order. X argues this parallel system enables unchecked censorship without proper oversight. The case, heard briefly by the Karnataka High Court, will continue on March 27. This legal challenge escalates X’s ongoing dispute with Prime Minister Modi’s government.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Modi’s government previously clashed with Twitter during the 2021 farmers' protests. The lawsuit also comes as Musk plans to expand Starlink and Tesla into India, raising the stakes of this confrontation. X is clashing with the directive, citing threats to free speech and user rights in India.</p>
        </mj-text>
