          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.5;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Earth Hour</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Summary: Many marked Earth Hour on Saturday by going dark to raise awareness for the climate crisis and environmental issues.</strong></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">On Saturday, people worldwide marked Earth Hour, a global campaign by the World Wildlife Foundation (WWF) to raise awareness of the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-24-03-2025-h3-3-climate-crisis-and-environmental-issues" target="_blank">climate crisis and environmental issues</a>. Iconic landmarks, including the Eiffel Tower, the Colosseum, the London Eye, the Sydney Opera House, and Berlin's Brandenburg Gate, went dark at 8:30 p.m. local time (3:30 a.m. in the US) in a symbolic show of support for the planet.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Earth Hour began in Australia in 2007 and has evolved into an annual event urging people to "give an hour for Earth" by reducing energy use or taking positive environmental actions. This year, participants sang songs at Berlin's Brandenburg Gate. WWF stresses the urgency of climate action. WWF cites 2024 as the hottest year on record. Rising global temperatures, wildfires, and extreme weather events threatening ecosystems contributed to this.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The event served as a reminder that even small actions count in protecting the planet’s future. Other environmentalists are critical of Earth Hour. The annual event puts the onus on individual behavior, while a small number of fossil fuel companies emit the vast majority of man-made carbon emissions.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
