              line-height: 1.5;
              border-left: 3px solid #4D3060;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
                    "><strong>The first weekend of the men’s NCAA Tournament is complete, and all second-round games are finished</strong>. The day began with the two-time defending champion Connecticut falling short against a high-powered Florida. Maryland narrowly avoided overtime and potential elimination with Derik Queen’s game-winning shot at the buzzer. The remaining 16 teams will get a break before play resumes on Thursday and Friday (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-24-03-2025-br8-11-more-highlights" target="_blank">more highlights</a>).</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.5;
              border-left: 3px solid #4D3060;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
                    "><strong>Ed Sheeran, supported by artists like Elton John and Harry Styles, is campaigning for $325 Mn in music education funding</strong> in the UK. Sheeran aims to improve school music provision, train teachers, and support grassroots venues. The campaign highlights the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-24-03-2025-br9-12-decline-in-music-education" target="_blank">decline in music education</a> and the importance of protecting the foundations.</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.5;
              border-left: 3px solid #4D3060;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
                    "><strong>After Ferrari and Lewis Hamilton’s heroics in the sprint race, the two Ferrari cars and Pierre Gasly’s Alpine were disqualified post-race</strong> from the Chinese GP. Leclerc and Gasly’s car breached <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-24-03-2025-br10-13-article-4-1-of-technical-regulations" target="_blank">Article 4.1 of the Technical Regulations</a>, while Hamilton’s car had excessive skid-block wear. Despite experiencing “nightmare” brake pedal issues, Lando Norris managed a P2 while his teammate, Oscar Piastri, raced to the chequered flag to finish P1.</p>
        </mj-text>
